{
  "local_port": 57610,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Why is my fridge not working but my freezer is?",
  "response": "If your refrigerator is not working but your freezer is, it could indicate a problem with the cooling system or components specific to the fridge section. Here are some possible causes and troubleshooting steps:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Defrost System Failure**\n   - The **defrost system** ensures frost doesn't build up on the evaporator coils. If it fails, frost can block airflow to the fridge while the freezer remains cold.\n   - **Check:** Look for frost buildup on the back wall of the freezer. If excessive, the defrost timer, defrost heater, or defrost thermostat may be faulty.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Evaporator Fan Malfunction**\n   - The **evaporator fan** circulates cold air from the freezer to the fridge. If it\u2019s not working, the fridge won\u2019t get cold.\n   - **Check:** Listen for the fan running when the fridge is on. If silent, the fan motor may need replacement.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Damper or Airflow Issue**\n   - The **damper** controls the flow of cold air from the freezer to the fridge. If it\u2019s stuck closed or blocked, the fridge won\u2019t cool.\n   - **Check:** Locate the damper (usually in the back or top of the fridge) and ensure it\u2019s open and unobstructed.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Thermostat or Temperature Control Problem**\n   - The fridge thermostat regulates cooling. If it\u2019s faulty, the fridge may not signal the compressor to cool.\n   - **Check:** Set the thermostat to the coldest setting and listen for the compressor to kick on. If it doesn\u2019t, the thermostat may need replacement.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Compressor or Refrigerant Issue**\n   - The **compressor** is the heart of the cooling system. If it\u2019s partially failing or there\u2019s a refrigerant leak, cooling may be uneven.\n   - **Check:** Listen for clicking sounds or unusual noises from the compressor. A professional may need to check refrigerant levels.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Blocked Vents**\n   - If the vents between the freezer and fridge are blocked, cold air won\u2019t reach the fridge.\n   - **Check:** Ensure vents in both the freezer and fridge sections are clear of food or ice.\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Condenser Coils Are Dirty**\n   - Dirty condenser coils can reduce cooling efficiency, though this usually affects both the fridge and freezer.\n   - **Check:** Clean the coils at the back or bottom of the fridge.\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Faulty Control Board or Sensors**\n   - Modern fridges use electronic control boards and sensors to manage cooling. A malfunctioning board or sensor can disrupt cooling.\n   - **Check:** If other components seem fine, the control board or sensors may need inspection by a technician.\n\n---\n\n### Next Steps:\n1. **Unplug the fridge** for safety before inspecting components.\n2. **Clear any frost or blockages** in the freezer and fridge vents.\n3. If you\u2019re unable to diagnose or fix the issue, contact a **qualified appliance repair technician**.\n\nLet me know if you need further guidance!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
